<HEADLINE> Philippine Health Chief Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Thursday said he has already accepted the resignation of
Felipe Estrella as secretary of health.
</P>
<P>
Estrada told reporters in an interview that he has assured
Estrella that the Presidential Palace would announce his
replacement "as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
But he did not identify Estrella's successor, saying only that
he is still scouting for a new secretary who is "pro-poor" and
whose expertise is on public health.
</P>
<P>
Estrella was reported to have submitted his resignation letter
to the president last week, but the chief executive's immediate
response was to ask him to go back to work and reconsider his
decision.
</P>
<P>
In subsequent media interviews, Estrella had claimed to have
formally asked Estrada to allow him to step down and retire from
public service so he could devote more time to his grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
"He said he was already sorry for his grandchildren. He could
no longer see them because he reports to his office at 5:30 a.m.,"
Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
"According to him, he is already old. He wants to spend the
rest of life with his children and grandchildren," Estrada said of
Estrella whose extensive record in public service include director
of the Philippine General Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
