<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Visits Three Flood-Stricken Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing has
urged governments of flood-stricken regions to fully implement
central government instructions regarding epidemic prevention and
extend every possible effort to prevent outbreaks of infectious
diseases.
</P>
<P>
Li visited evacuation centers, temporary medical stations and
schools during his four-day fact-finding tour of Jiangxi, Hunan
and Hubei province, three areas sustaining the heaviest damage
from this summer's heavy flooding.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier called on officials and medical personnel to
promote a greater awareness of the need for personal hygiene and
sanitation. He also noted the importance of properly disposing of
waste and night soil in order to prevent epidemics.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that efforts should center on closely monitoring
epidemic conditions in disaster areas and pointed the need for
adequate medical supplies and instruments to prevent outbreaks of
infectious diseases.
</P>
<P>
Li called on local governments to ensure that schools open on
schedule. He said priority should be placed on repairing or
rebuilding school facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
