<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Rises 31.98 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Thursday closed at 2918.89,
showing a rise of 31.98 points from the previous close of 2886.91.
</P>
<P>
The national index ended with a gain of 11.59 points at 1302.35
from the last close of 1290.76.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 closed higher at 302.19 and the U.S. dollar index
at 118.21 from the last closes of 300.38 and 117.59 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Stocks scored further gains in Bombay Thursday on hectic short
covering and speculative buying by domestic institutions and funds
prompted by the fresh recovery in the global markets and the calm
on the local political front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
