<HEADLINE> Greek Industrial Production Increases Significantly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Greece's industrial production
increased by 4.5 percent during the first half of this year
compared with the same period in 1997, the Greek National
Statistics Service (NSS) announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In June this year, the country's industrial production rose to
6.4 percent compared to the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The NSS attributed the rise in industrial production to the
devaluation of the national currency, drachma, last March which
boosted exports, and to the increase in exports to eastern
countries, especially those made during the first six months.
</P>
</TEXT>
