<HEADLINE> Clinton to Send Envoy Ross to Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton is
to send U.S. special envoy Dennis Ross to the Middle East next
week to help push ahead the deadlocked Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Mike McCurry was quoted by Reuters as
saying Thursday that the resumption of direct high-level U.S.
involvement in the talks was at the request of both Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat.
</P>
