<DOCNO> XIE19980904.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Has Enough Fertilizers for Winter Crops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Agriculture Minister
Trilochan Dhakal said here Thursday that there will be no shortage
of chemical fertilizers for winter crops in the country.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the official RSS news agency as telling the
Lower House of Parliament that there used to be a shortage of
fertilizers in the country, but as the private sector has been
provided license for import of fertilizers, the supply system has
been strengthened.
</P>
<P>
At present the country has a stock of urea, potassium and other
chemical fertilizers and the private sector is importing
additional fertilizers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Inadequate supply of fertilizers used to be a serious problem
in Nepal, where 82 percent of the population depends on
agriculture for livelihood.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, the government formulated new policies
involving the private sector in importing fertilizers, thus
breaking the monopoly of the state-owned Agricultural Inputs
Corporation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
