<HEADLINE> Envoy Expected to Discuss Nigerian-Canadian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the Canadian
government are expected in Nigeria next Monday to discuss the
restoration of diplomatic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to reliable sources, David Kilgour, Secretary of
State for Africa and Latin America, is to head the delegation.
</P>
<P>
Canada closed its embassy in Nigeria early last year as its
staff were allegedly unsafe following a spate of bomb blasts in
Nigeria and attacks on the Canadian embassy.
</P>
<P>
In September 1996, Nigeria closed its mission, saying that
Nigeria's economy could no longer sustain the maintenance of a
large number of diplomatic missions and personnel abroad.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy said on August 24
that his country would move to restore ties with Nigeria and be
offering financial and technical assistance towards successful
implementation of Nigeria's transition program.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy attributed the intention to restore relations with
Nigeria to measures taken by the present government to restore
democracy in the West African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
