<HEADLINE> Uganda's Population to Reach 22M in 2000: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's population which is
currently put at 21.1 million is expected to grow to more than 22
million in 2000, a population report has said.
</P>
<P>
According to the state of the world report launched Wednesday
evening by Finance Minister Gerald Sendaula, the population
growth rate in Uganda stands at 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Radio Uganda reported Thursday evening that the minister has
urged every Ugandan to join the government in its effort to plan
for the reduction of the current population growth rate.
</P>
<P>
There has been no birth control program in Uganda where
polygamy is widely observed.
</P>
<P>
Families in the countryside tend to be very big although those
in cities are now apt to become smaller due to the heavy burden
of supporting large families.
</P>
<P>
Overpopulation is looming as a potential threat to Uganda's
future economic growth and now the government is encouraging
people to raise their living standards instead of giving birth to
many babies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
