<HEADLINE> Israel Hopes to Enhance Trade Ties With Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Ambassador to Cyprus
Shemi Tzur stressed here Thursday the need of enhancing the trade
ties between Israel and Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Tzur made the remarks at a seminar on business opportunities in
Israel, which started Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tzur said business contacts between the two countries have
increased impressively over the past years, with the trade volume
reaching 158 million U.S. dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus is on the verge of joining the European Union, and with
its advantageous geographic location, it can serve as an ideal
bridge between Israel and the European countries, Tzur said.
</P>
<P>
"Closer commercial ties between our two countries will lead to
larger market access for Cypriot businessmen and in turn give
Israeli companies access to European and Middle East locations,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador expected that the seminar would promote the
understanding between business societies of the two countries,
and give Cypriots insight into the business opportunities and
prospects in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tzur spoke highly of the forthcoming economic
conference in Jerusalem in October, saying such a gathering would
provide an opportunity for businessmen across the world to expand
trade cooperation with the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus' relations with Israel have been enhanced since it
opened up an embassy in Tel Aviv five years ago and through the
exchange of visits by high-ranking officials.
