<HEADLINE> Boutros Boutros-Ghali to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Jean Chretien
announced Thursday that Secretary General of La Francophonie
Boutros Boutros-Ghali will visit Canada from September 6 to 15,
1998.
</P>
<P>
"It gives the Secretary General a chance to see Canada's
vigorous francophone heritage and to discuss francophone issues
from an international perspective," said the Prime Minister in a
release.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Canada, Secretary General Boutros-Ghali will
visit Moncton, Province of New Brunswick, site of the eighth
Francophone Summit to be held September 3 to 5, 1999. A central
theme of the summit is youth, which the Secretary General will be
discussing with Canadian officials.
</P>
<P>
In addition to meeting with the Prime Minister, the Secretary
General will meet with Governor General Romeo LeBlanc, members of
the federal Cabinet, including Foreign Affairs Minister Lloyd
Axworthy and Minister for International Co-operation and Minister
responsible for La Francophonie Diane Marleau, as well as the
Premiers of New Brunswick and Quebec.
</P>
<P>
La Francophonie boasts 52 member states and governments that
share French as a common language. Canada was a founding member of
this organization, which evolved from the Agency for Cultural and
Technical Co-operation created in 1970. 
</P>
