<HEADLINE> One Killed, 12 Injured as Lesotho Police Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was
killed and 12 others injured Thursday evening when Lesotho police
opened fire on a crowd of protesters outside the royal palace in
Maseru, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted an unnamed diplomatic source as saying that police
opened fire on about 500 people at about 5 p.m. (1500 GMT) after
shots were fired from the crowd.
</P>
<P>
The source could not confirm reports that the shooting
involved soldiers and police firing at each other.
</P>
<P>
Supporters of the three main opposition parties have camped
outside King Letsie III's palace since August 4 to protest the
results of the May 23 general election.
</P>
<P>
They claim that the results were rigged in favor of the ruling
Lesotho Congress for Democracy which won 79 of 80 seats in the
National Assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
