<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Die in UK Road Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- British police are
investigating the scene of the crash near Great Yarmouth in which
three members of the same family died after their car collided
with a coach.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened on a dangerous stretch of the A12 south
of Great Yarmouth in east coast of England. Both vehicles were
travelling south towards Lowestoft when the collision happened,
police said.
</P>
<P>
A father and two of his children -- 13-year old daughter and
seven-year old son -- were killed instantly. Two other children --
one a baby and the other aged four -- were seriously injured, and
are being treated at a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the single-decker coach overturned after colliding
with the car at about 4.15 pm.
</P>
<P>
The passengers on the coach and its driver received minor
injuries and were also taken to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Fire Brigade said it had sent two fire engines and used
hydraulic cutting equipment to release some of the victims.
</P>
<P>
Police say the A12 southbound will be closed well into the
evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
