<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kohl and His Rival in Pre-Election Duel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- German Chanceller Helmut Kohl and
his election contender Gerhard Schroeder Thursday engaged in their
only face-to-face debate before the September general elections,
both portraying themselves as the right choice to lead Germany
into the next century.
</P>
<P>
With the German national elections just 24 days away, Kohl's
centre-right ruling coalition and the main opposition Social
Democratic Party (SPD) on Thursday made the last session of the
current German parliament into a battle field to vie for voters'
support.
</P>
<P>
In his hour-long speech to the parliament, Kohl drew a positive
balance of his 16-year leadership and described his
conservatives-led ruling coalition as the security anchor for
Germany in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Brushing aside attacks on his failure to cut Germany's
record-high unemployment, Kohl stressed that reforms conducted by
his government had brought about not only a recovery in the
economy, but also a trend reversal on the job market.
</P>
<P>
He also attacked Schroeder as being ambiguous in his policies.
"The country needs sound and solid policies, not experiments,"
Kohl said.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Schroeder described Kohl as "a chancellor of
unemployment" and a worn-out politician who lost his grasp of
Germany's current social problems after 16 years in power.
</P>
<P>
"Your record is modest, therefore Germany cannot afford another
four years of Kohl," Schroeder said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing his party's faith in Germany's social welfare system,
Schroeder also vowed to conduct his own reforms to combine
modernity with more social justice.
</P>
<P>
With the election day approaching, Kohl is still trailing
Schroeder by three to six percentage points in opinion polls,
though the gap has been narrowed when compared with earlier this
year.
</P>
<P>
Betting his chances on many voters who have not made up their
mind, Kohl has stressed the election would be decided only in the
final weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
