<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, September 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma decided on Friday to postpone
the second round of vote on Viktor Chernomyrdin's nomination as
prime minister to next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The postponement was made at a request of the Russian president.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma, or lower house of parliament, took the
decision with 294 votes for, 51 against and three abstaining.
(Russia-Duma-Postponement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- The Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
sent its first artificial satellite into orbit on August 31,
transmitting revolutionary songs back to the Earth, the Korean
Central News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A three-stage rocket carrying the satellite blasted off in the
direction of 86 degrees at a launching station in the Musudan-ri
village, Hwadae County, North Hamgyong Province at about 12
a.m. local time (0300 GMT). (DPRK-Satellite)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German central bank president Hans Tietmeyer has said
that he did not expect the financial crises in Russia and Asia to
trigger a global recession, German media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to financial journalists Thursday evening in
Frankfurt, Tietmeyer said that despite all the challenges, the
euro zone had retained a "relatively high degree of stability"
with sustained growth clearly under way.
</P>
<P>
Growth in the United States was also continuing despite the
economic problems in other regions, Tietmeyer added.
(Germany-Global Crisis-Unlikely)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Hunger and disease have killed at least 100 people,
mostly children, over the past two weeks in rebel-held Kailahun
district of Sierra Leone, health officials in the eastern part of
the country said.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Friday quoted authorities in Kenema, 240
kilometers east of Freetown, capital of Sierra Leone, as saying
that the deaths from starvation and diarrhoea disease occurred in
the Kailahun district which is a bastion of the country's
rebels. (Sierra Leone-Deaths) 
</P>
</TEXT>
