<HEADLINE> Chinese Shuttlers March to Asian Badminton Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese shuttlers edged
their ways to all five finals in the 136,000 US dollars JVC Asian
Badminton Championships after winning their semi-finals
respectively here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhaoyin luckily entered the women's singles' final after
Dai Yun, another Chinese player quit the semi-final because of
illness.
</P>
<P>
Ye will vie for the title against Gong Zhichao, also Chinese,
who won over her teammate Gong Ruina in the semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Chen Gang of China ousted his compatriot Luo Yigang and will
meet Marleve Mainaky of Indonesia to vie for the men's singles
title after Mainaky upstaged another Idonesian player Taufik
Hidayat in another semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The men's double semi-final match pitted Chinese Zhang Jun and
Zhang Wei against Indonesia Flandy Limpele and Eng Hian for a
fierce battle which the Chinese duo won eventually 17-15, 9-15
and 15-12.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jun and Zhang Wei will compete, in the final match of
men's double, against South Korean Kang Kyung Jin and Ha Tae Kwon
who crushed Indonesian Tony Gunawan and Halim Heryanto for
another final berth.
</P>
<P>
Ge Fei and Gu Jun edged Indonesian Elysa and Deyana Lomban in
the women's doubles semi-final, while their teammates Qing Yiyuan
and Tang Hetian overpowered South Korean Yimkyung Jin and Chung
Jae Hee.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Li Yongbo told Xinhua that up to now he was
generally satisfied with the performance of the Chinese players
who he said had given full play to their skills in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
But Li said top Chinese shuttler Sun Jun's defeat to
Indonesian Marleve Mainaky showed that Sun lacked "systematic and
scientific training".
</P>
<P>
Marleve, ranking 15th in the world, eliminated Sun, winner of
this year's All-England, from the men's signle semi-final on
Thursday. 
</P>
