<HEADLINE> Men's Top Two Seeds Advance, Two Women's Seeds Fail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, CHINA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Top two seeds Kong
Linghui and Liu Guoliang advanced to the third round of the
Chinese Table Tennis Grand Prix while their fellow Chinese Wang
Chen and Yang Ying, seeded second and third respectively, were
eliniminated in their openers here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kong, ranked third in the world, had little trouble in the
first set, beating Poland 's L. Blaszczyk 21-13.
</P>
<P>
But Blazczyk, who set up the clash with the 1995 world
champion after beating qualifier K. Nakamura of Japan earlier,
fought back in the second when Kong made a lot of errors, winning
21-16.
</P>
<P>
Kong, who won the Australia Open last week, regained his
rhythm again and overwhelmed the Polish in the last two sets
21-14, 21-11 with his solid defence and strong topspin attack.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Liu held off fierce challenge from
chopper-plus-attacker Syed Matthew of England in the first two
sets before advancing to the third round with a 21-15, 21-15,
21-13 straight victory.
</P>
<P>
World No.5 Liu, well known for his wickedly deceptive service,
was forced into many errors by the patient Matthew. Liu had to
match the unknown English Paddler stroke for stroke and the two
sides exchanged lead time and again in the beginning of the first
two sets.
</P>
<P>
Matthew, a winner over qualifer N. Tsiokas of Greece in the
first round, faded in the last set before the powerful smash of
his Chinese oppenent, a beaten semifinalist in the Australia Open.
</P>
<P>
Wang and Yang, ranked fourth and sixth respectively in the
world , became the day's two biggest casualties, with Wang losing
to K. Okazaki 19-21, 24-22, 21-16, 19-21, 16-21, and Yang to Song
Ah Sim 17-21, 21-14, 21-14, 17-21, 15-21 in the women's second
round competition.
</P>
<P>
The 61,000 U.S. dollars event, to run until Sunday, has attra
cted 140 players from 25 countries and regions, all of them
inside the 100 rankings. Winner of the men's singles event will
get a prize money of 10,000 while the women's winner will take
8,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
