<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Three-time Olympic champion
Michelle Smith-De Bruin has lodged a suit against her four-year
suspension by FINA, the swimming's governing body, the Court of
Arbitration for Sports (CAS) said at Lausanne on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Irish swimmer was expected to submit an appeal with the
Lausanne-based court before September 6 after FINA found her
guilty of tampering with a urine sample taken to test for drugs.
</P>
<P>
Smith-De Bruin has insisted that she did not interfere with
the sample and has said she would seek damages.
</P>
<P>
The CAS will hold a hearing in Lausanne after both Smith-De
Bruin and FINA turn in their written statements.
</P>
<P>
A panel of arbitrators will review the evidence and must issue
a decison within four months of receiving the appeal. 
