<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Lauds Medical Team Working in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing today
praised a state medical team working in the Tibet Autonomous
Region and expressed great appreciation for their efforts to
help local cataract patients regain their vision.
</P>
<P>
He also congratulated patients who have recovered from the
surgical procedure.
</P>
<P>
The medical team, organized by the Ministry of Health and the
China Disabled Persons' Federation, arrived in Tibet on August 23
and have since examined some 1,500 cataract patients. The team has
provided free operations for 340 people.
