<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic
briefs from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
RABAT -- Arab investments in Morocco last year restored the
vigor lost in the past few years to reach some 328 million
U.S. dollars, the Arabic daily Al Hayat reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The figures did not include the private projects undertaken by
prominent Arab personalities.
</P>
<P>
Libya tops the list of Arab investments in Morocco as its
investments reached 238 million dollars. Libyan funds were also
active, particularly through third parties, in the Moroccan
finance markets.
</P>
