week as the the general index sharply declined due to the
worldwide fall triggered by Russian turmoil.
</P>
<P>
The shares of the banking sector was particularly hit hard. But
the market soon restored balance by the weekend, with the general
index closing at 165.2 points Thursday as compared to 169.81
points at the previous week's closing.
</P>
<P>
RIYADH -- Saudi Arabia's second Deputy Prime Minister Prince
Sultan Bin Abdul Aziz will inaugurate a series of projects that
cost 2 billion rials (533 million dollars) in the region of Al
Qaseem during his visit to the area which started Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Prince Faisal Bin Bandar, emir of Al Qaseem region, has
disclosed that the value of projects in the region over the past
six years has surpassed 6.6 billion rials (1,76 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- The state-owned Kuwait Investment Company (KIC)
Thursday sold 125 million shares, each valued at about 1
U.S. dollar, to the Gulf International Investment Company as part
of the privatization scheme, the Kuwait News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The shares, sold at an auction held at the Kuwait Stock
Exchange, accounted for 25 percent of the KIC's total shares, said
Abdul Salam Al-Awadhi, the company's Board Chairman.
</P>
<P>
He said another 250 million of the KIC shares will be put for
public subscription. The KIC, established in 1961, is the first
Kuwaiti investment company. 
