<HEADLINE> Japanese Statesmen Donate to China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Japanese lawmakers of both
houses of the Diet (parliament) on Thursday donated 3.76 million
yen (about 28,060 U.S. dollars) to help flood victims in China.
</P>
<P>
House of Representatives speaker Soichiro Ito and House of
Councillors president Juro Saito, on behalf of 752 members from
both chambers, handed the sum to Chinese Ambassador to Japan Chen
Jian at the Diet building.
</P>
<P>
Ito expressed sympathy to the Chinese people struck by floods
and hoped people in the flood-ravaged areas could rebuild their
homes as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Chen briefed the two parliamentary leaders on the Chinese
people's fight against the floods and expressed appreciation to
Japanese politicians for their assistance.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Embassy to Japan has received nearly 100 million
yen (about 746,000 dollars) in donation from Japan's
non-governmental organizations, companies and individuals as of
Friday, according to embassy officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
