<HEADLINE> Int'l Federation of Stock Exchanges Workshop in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The International Federation
of Stock Exchanges (FIBV) concluded a two-day workshop here Friday
on how to foster relations between exchanges and issuers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 52 delegates from all over the world took part in
the workshop entitled "Stock Exchange -- Issuer Relations", said
Gerrit H. de Marez Oyens, FIBV Secretariat General, at a press
conference here.
</P>
<P>
He said participants exchanged views on how to build good
relations with listed companies since they came to realize that
marketing and communications made an important part of business
for stock exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Originally created by 10 European Stock Exchanges in 1961, the
Paris-based FIBV now has 51 members, which represent 95 percent of
the world's market capitalization. 
</P>
