<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed sharply higher Friday.
</P>
<P>
Finance stocks led the surge where huge demands were seen
sparked by Malaysian National Bank's announcement Thursday of a
further 1.50 points cut in the three-month intervention rate to
eight percent, according to dealers.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was pushed
up 16.1 percent or 50.37 points to 363.44, the all-share Emas
Index rose 12.99 points to 95.81, the Industrial Index rebounded
115.56 points to 729.42 and the Second Board Index increased by
10.62 points to 90.31.
</P>
<P>
Advancers whacked decliners 523 to 10 while seven counters were
unchanged, 74 untraded and 24 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover surged to 522.449 million shares valued at
617.556 million ringgit (162.514 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 310.413 million shares worth 377.453 million ringgit
(99.329 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Main Board enlarged to 498.522 million shares
valued at 590.509 million ringgit (155.397 million U.S. dollars)
from 299.397 million shares valued at 366.594 million ringgit
(96.472 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Second Board improved to 23.928 million shares
valued at 24.047 million ringgit (6.328 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 11.016 million shares worth 10.859 million ringgit
(2.857 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals fell to 678,000 shares valued at 2.016 million
ringgit (0.53 million U.S. dollars) from 5.980 million shares
valued at 7.639 million ringgit (2.01 million U.S. dollars) on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 20.726
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
40.197 million shares, construction 63.296 million shares,
trade/services 160.208 million shares, infrastructures 1.465
million shares, finance 107.783 million shares, hotels 926,000
shares, properties 41.078 million shares, plantation 7.984 million
shares, mining 1.037 million shares, trusts 362,00 shares,
closed/fund 210,000 shares and loans 53.250 million shares.
</P>
