<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Strikes Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.6
on the Richter scale Thursday night hit Solukhumbu district, about
160 kilometers east of Kathmandu, the official RSS news agency
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was in the neighborhood of Mt. Chamlang in the
north-east of the district, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was felt in the capital city as well.
</P>
<P>
A Home Ministry spokesman told Xinhua that the ministry
contacted the district officer but there was no information yet
about damage or casualties.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 5.0 on the Richter scale can cause
moderate damage in a built-up area.
</P>
<P>
Several minor earthquakes have struck the Himalayan kingdom
this year.
</P>
<P>
Both local and international seismic experts had predicted a
considerably large-scale earthquake in the near future in the
Kathmandu Valley, which lies in the seismic belt.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 8.4 on the Richter scale rocked Nepal
on January 15, 1934, claiming 4,296 lives.
</P>
<P>
Another earthquake in 1989, measuring 6.4 on the Richter scale,
killed about 700 people in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
