<HEADLINE> First Web Department Store In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
financial and commercial city, has just opened its first on-line
department store.
</P>
<P>
The Yixiang Shopping Center launched its Internet site on
September 1, offering about 1,000 items for sale to Web users.
The number of commodities for sale on the site is expected to
increase to 10,000 by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Yixiang Web shopping system was jointly developed by the
Shanghai Commercial Information Center and China Textiles
University.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, Shanghai has set up a number of shops on the Web,
including a bookstore, flower shop and drugstore.
</P>
<P>
Some local observers believe that the number of department
store customers in Shanghai will decline by 20 to 30 percent by
the end of the century due to the growth of on-line shopping and
electronic businesses.  
