<HEADLINE> Laos, U.S. Conduct Joint Search for U.S. MIA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Debris of aircraft and remains
of U.S. pilots have been found in joint search conducted by Laos
and U.S. for American Missing In Action (MIA) personnel in Laos
during the war period, Lao official Khaosan Pathet Lao news agency
(KPL) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The discoveries will be sent to the United States for analysis,
said KPL.
</P>
<P>
Lao and American technical teams conducted 21 joint searches in
Houaphanh and Xieng Khouang provinces and the Vientiane prefecture
from July 28 to August 29.
</P>
<P>
The teams also conducted five excavations in Savannakhet
province during the period.
</P>
<P>
The surveys and excavations were the fifth operations under the
joint action plan for 1997-1998.
</P>
<P>
KPL said that the joint operations were conducted in line with
the humanitarian policy of the Lao government and the 1997-1998
bilateral cooperation plan. 
</P>
