<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 2.32 Percent Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hang Seng Index of 33
blue chips rose 169.88 points, or 2.32 percent, to close at
7,488.47 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Despite a weak opening following overnight falls on Wall
Street, the market recouped earlier losses on bargain hunting and
short covering, brokers said.
</P>
<P>
Utilities and commerce and industry sectors drove the key
barometer up. Utilities shares soared 539.12 points, or 5.2
percent while commerce and industry shares went up 183.74 points,
or 4.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The value of turnover amounted to 6,851 million HK dollars (878
million U.S. dollars), compared with 6,325 million HK dollars (811
million U.S. dollars) the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said China-related shares were the focus of the market
Friday as investors were expecting a further cut in interest rates
in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index, or H shares, shot 35.59
points, or 13.35 percent, to close at 302.21 while Hang Seng
China-Affiliated Corporations Index, or red chips, soaring 88.88
points, or 14.95 percent, to end of 683.55.
</P>
<P>
Combining the five trading days of the week together, the Hang
Seng Index fell 341.27 points, or 4.4 percent. 
</P>
