<HEADLINE> Lesotho Police, Soldiers Trade Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho police and
soldiers were engaged in heavy shooting Friday outside King
Letsie III's palace in Maseru as hundreds of people made their
way to work, South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Along Maseru's main street, Kingsway, vehicles turned back as
intense bursts from machine-guns were heard at about 7.30 a.m.,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said a policeman was seriously injured in the
shooting, and windows at an office block near the palace were
shattered by bullets.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers guarding the palace gate allegedly fired at a group
of police as they tried to remove a land rover outside the palace
gate, where it had been parked since Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
It was earlier reported that one person was killed and more
than 10 others were injured Thursday when police and soldiers
clashed outside the palace.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's shooting started at about 5 p.m. and continued for
about three hours. It sent a crowd of about 500 people, who were
protesting against the results of Lesotho's May election outside
the palace, cowering for cover behind the palace wall.
</P>
<P>
It appeared that soldiers guarding the palace fired on police
after they opened fire on the protesters, and they opened the
gates of the palace to let the crowd in to escape the gunfire,
some reports said.
</P>
<P>
There has been no official report on the incident from the
police.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho has been volatile since August 4 when the country's
opposition parties staged protests against the ruling Lesotho
Congress for Democracy's landslide victory in the May polls.
Opposition parties claimed the polls were rigged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
