<HEADLINE> Inflation Down in Philippine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' year-on-year
inflation rate went down to 10.5 percent last month from 10.7
percent in July, based on the 1994 basket of commodities, the
National Statistics Office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A report from the office also showed that the inflation rate
from January to August stood at 9.3 percent, still within the
government target of a single-digit inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
The month-on-month inflation rate in August, however, rose to
0.5 percent compared to 0.2 percent the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The rates for food, beverages and tobacco slowed down to 9.7
percent in August from 10 percent in July. The rates for clothing,
fuel, light and water also dropped.
</P>
<P>
Other groups including housing and repairs, services and
miscellaneous registered higher inflation rates in August.
</P>
</TEXT>
