<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
began his official visit to the Irish Republic on Friday by
holding talks with Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern.
</P>
<P>
Clinton arrived in the republic Thursday evening after ending
his one-day trip to Northern Ireland where he toured provincial
capital Belfast and western town Omagh, a place of last month's
blast that killed 28 people.
</P>
<P>
During Friday's talks, Clinton and Ahern were expected to
discuss the peace process, including security measures approved in
London and Dublin which the countries' leaders have described as
"draconian."
</P>
<P>
