Ireland and it had not been expected to match the excitement of
late 1995 when thousands of people turned out to see the president
who had made ending the "troubles" in the north a focus of his
foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and Ahern planned to attend a reception together
with several hundred people from Ireland's government, business,
trade union and farming communities.
</P>
<P>
Later on Friday, Clinton was expected to visit the European
center of U.S. computer company Gateway 2000 on the outskirts of
Dublin.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Clinton will visit the western city of Limerick
and then get in his game of golf before heading back to
Washington. 
</P>
