<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Gains in August From Easing of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market
marked an ascending course in August amidst vivid investment
activities triggered by easing of the political tension, a monthly
market report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market review, issued by Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), said the CISCO All-Share Index
closed on August 31 at 446.4 points, registering a notable monthly
rise of 23.3 points, or 5.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the level of 440 points was surpassed for the
first time since mid-May when the market was experiencing a steep
decline due to the tension sparked by Cyprus' determination to
deploy the Russian-made anti-aircraft missiles as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
The highest monthly level was recorded on August 27 when the
market closed at 451.9 points, which is only 22 points short of
this year's record of 473.9 points.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the market engaged on a gradual unwinding which
naturally follows periods of continuous and uninterrupted
ascents. Therefore, the market lost some ground and the CISCO
All-Share Index closed on Thursday at 442 points.
</P>
<P>
The review said that investment euphoria during August was
primarily supported by the easing of political tension regarding
the issue of the arrival of the Russian-made S-300 missiles,
which seems at present to be shelved.
</P>
<P>
Investors seemed to be relieved from the latest
developments. And as soon as the possibility of postponing the
missile deployment emerged, they rushed in, channeling their
available funds towards selected stocks, the review said.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions for August soared to 25.2
million Cyprus pounds (about 50.4 million U.S. dollars) from
19.9 million pounds (39.8 million dollars) in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
