<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Falling in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices continued falling
in Tokyo Friday as the collapse of Toa Steel Co. and the sharp
drop in Wall Street overnight depressed investors.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange fell 218.33 points, or 1.53
percent, from Thursday's close to end at 14,042.91.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, lost 19.30 points or 1.73 percent to
1,094.47.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the major section went up to an estimated 430 million
shares from Thursday's 376.02 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toa Steel's decision late Thursday to fold next March made it
the fifth listed Japanese company this year to go belly up and
dealt a strong blow to steel shares. Its parent company, NKK, was
the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the 1.29 percent decline in the Dow Jones Industrial
Average in New York spurred selling in shares of multinational
blue chips.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,341 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outpaced gainers 972 to 196, with 118 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
