<HEADLINE> Swissair Offers Immediate Compensation to Air Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Swissair will compensate
relatives of passengers on flight SR 111 for compensatory damages
under the applicable law, said the Swiss airline in a press
release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"In order to help meet the immediate financial need that may be
experienced by relatives of the passengers on board flight SR 111,
Swissair will, as soon as possible, make payments of CHF 30,000 or
20,000 U.S. dollars in respect of each passenger, should they wish
this," the company said.
</P>
<P>
All of the 229 people on board of the Swiss MD-11, including 215
passengers and 14 crew members, died in a crash Thursday morning off
in the Atlantic ocean off eastern Canada.
</P>
<P>
Letters are being sent to relatives of all the passengers inviting
them, or their representatives, to contact the company if they wish to
take advantage of this.
</P>
<P>
Claims of the passengers' families are subject to the Warsaw
Convention and to the General Conditions of Carriage of
Swissair. 
</P>
