The moves will affect 92 Defense Department employees and 150
local nationals, the Pentagon said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the sites will be vacated by U.S. forces and
returned to the control of the host nations as part of the
Pentagon's 23rd round of closures of overseas facilities.
</P>
<P>
(US-Military Sites)
</P>
<P>
