VIENNA -- Austrian Chancellor Viktor Klima said Thursday
Austria was working with the other 14 European Union members to
prepare a statement on Russia's situation.
</P>
<P>
Klima, who is rotating president of the European Union, urged
Russia on behalf of the EU to continue its reform. He said the EU
must send all Russian parties a signal that reform was
irreversible and only with this condition would the international
community continue its financial aid. (Austria-Russia)
</P>
