<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang's Border Trade Volume Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The border trade volume of
northermost Heilongjiang Province totaled 660.9 million U.S.
dollars in the first seven months of this year, according to
official statistics. This total includes 218.28 million U.S.
dollars in imports and 442.67 million U.S. dollars in exports, up
8.12 percent and 27.6 percent respectively from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Ji Qingfu, director of the provincial border trade bureau, said
that 124 contracts for economic and technical cooperation were
signed in the January-July period, a rise of 27.66 percent on a
yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
These contracts are valued at 46.77 million U.S. dollars, a
jump of 66.2 percent from a year ago, Ji added.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang's major imports include pulp, raw chemical
materials, timber, fertilizer and non-ferrous metals, while
exports include garments, textiles, foodstuffs, light industrial
products, and grain and edible oil, according to Ji. 
</P>
</TEXT>
