<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Guangzhou up 22.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 4 (Xinhua) -- This capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, a showcase of the country's market
reform program, utilized 1.91 billion U.S. dollars in overseas
funds in the first seven months of this year, a surge of 22.5
percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's number of overseas-funded projects with a total
investment worth more than 10 million U.S. dollars each had
reached 1,045 by the end of June, an increase of 34 from a year
ago, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in Guangzhou has increased this year in
almost all sectors, with contracted investment in industrial
projects totaling 555 million U.S. dollars while that in the real
estate sector amounted to 320 million U.S. dollars, official
figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, investment from southeast Asia plummeted
while that from Europe and the United States rose
steadily. European companies invested 120.3 million U.S. dollars
in Guangzhou in the first seven months, a jump of 60.6 percent,
while investment by firms from the United States rocketed 86.9
percent to 71.27 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
