<HEADLINE> Croatia, Bosnia Reach Seaports Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Croatia and Bosnia agreed in
principle on Thursday to allow each to use the other's seaports.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Bosnia can use the Croatian port of Ploce
to reach the sea. In exchange, its Neum will be used by Croatia to
link southern and northern Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached after talks in the Croatian seaside
city of Dubruvnik between Nenad Porges, Croatian Economic
Minister, and Mirsad Kurtovic, Bosnian Foreign Trade and
International Economic Cooperation Minister.
</P>
<P>
The accord was based on the 1994 Washington Agreement and the
1995 Dayton Peace Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to hold further discussions on the concrete
issues this weekend in Sarajevo and Zagreb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
