<HEADLINE> Rio Group Urged to Increase Dialogue with Other Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of Chile and
Panama said Thursday the Group of Rio should increase dialogues
and political coordination with other regions.
</P>
<P>
They made the statement in a joint declaration issued when
Chilean President Eduardo Frei Ruiz-Tagle was paying a two-day
visit to Panama.
</P>
<P>
Frei will also attend the 12th summit meeting of the Group of
Rio, which will open here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said they also discussed the return of Panama
Canal and expressed their support to legislative measures taken by
the Panama government to manage the canal.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian President Ernesto Perez Balladares said in the
declaration that Panama will provide Chile with facilities needed
for the return of the canal and would seek economic cooperation
with Chile in the canal zone.
</P>
<P>
Frei is the first Chilean president to have visited Panama. His
visit is aimed at improving trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are now negotiating on a free trade agreement
which is expected to be concluded by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Annual trade between the two countries maintains at about 265
million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
