<DOCNO> XIE19980904.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Distributes Relief Grains, Money Among Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi Ministry of
Relief and Disaster Management has so far distributed 43.45
million taka (924,450 U.S. dollars) in cash and 66,018 tons of
rice among the flood victims.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by the state minister of the ministry at a
meeting of the Parliamentary Standing Committee on the ministry
held here Thursday, press reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government has decided to distribute more vulnerable group
feeding (VGF) cards among the flood-affected people especially in
the worst-hit areas of the country, the reports quoted the state
minister of the ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Three hundred people of every flood-hit unions (townships) are
now holding VGF cards, while each of them receive about 15
kilograms of rice per month, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government has so far distributed a total of 777,470 VGF
cards among the poor and it would start distributing more cards
soon, he stated.
</P>
<P>
More than 21.5 million people have been affected by the current
devastating floods in the country since July 12 in 45 of the
country's 64 districts, with the death toll rising to 451 so far.
</P>
<P>
The country's food aid requirement has been estimated to be
around 1.38 million tons in the current fiscal year since crop
loss caused by nearly two-month-long floods might stand at three
million tons because 60 percent of rice crop has been severely
affected.
</P>
<P>
Besides the food aid, the country will require a 630 million
dollar-aid from outside for post-flood rehabilitation work, and
foreign aid for Bangladeshi flood victims has so far reached 84
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
