<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Satisfied with Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 60 percent of foreign
investors are satisfied with the financial environment in
Bulgaria, according to a new survey.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian Telegraph Agency, which conducted the survey,
announced that foreign investors showed the most interest in
tourism, agriculture, light industry and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors listed high standards education, low labor
costs and the proximity to large neighboring markets as reasons to
come to Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
But they complained about certain laws and regulations, the
inefficiency of official institutions, out-of-date infrastructure,
relatively high taxes, and the poor local market.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria is among the Eastern European countries attracting the
lowest amount of foreign over recent years because of a poor
investment environment. Foreign investment totaled only 700
million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
But foreign investors were given many new advantages after the
Bulgarian parliament passed the Foreign Investment Law last
December. 
</P>
