<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Persistent Efforts Urged to Achieve Full Victory over Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Water
Resources Niu Maosheng urged flood-fighters to remain alert and to
exert themselves to achieve a complete victory.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with "People's Daily," Niu, who is also deputy
commander-in-chief of the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters, said flood-fighting has been a success so far, but
vigilance must remain high receding water levels in Yangtze River,
Nenjiang and Songhua rivers. Embankments, which have soaked in
floodwaters for extended days, are prone to collapse and could
cause major damage in the later periods of the flood season.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the 3,600 kilometers of main
embankments built along the Yangtze and major dikes built along
Dongting and Poyang lakes have been containing floodwaters which
have exceeded the danger line for more than 60 days. In some
places, more than 300 kilometers of secondary dikes have been
built to hold back floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
And the main levee built along the Songhua River has also been
operating for over one month with water levels above the danger
line. To hold back floodwaters, 600 kilometers of additional dikes
have been constructed along the river.
</P>
<P>
To achieve a complete victory against flooding in forthcoming
days, it is essential to increase meteorological and hydrological
forecasts and monitoring in accordance with the development of
floods and to intensify flood management, said Niu.
</P>
<P>
Different localities should continue to patrol the main
embankments around the clock, he said, and effective measures
should be practiced to prevent collapse while the floodwaters
recede. Materials for rescue work should be made ready for actions
when necessary, he added.
</P>
<P>
Niu also called for construction of water control facilities
across the country after the flood season is over. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
