<HEADLINE> Chirac Gives Moral Support on Ukraine Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 3 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
called on Thursday for Russia to carry out urgently needed
economic reforms while praising the progress made in neighboring
Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Chirac, who arrived in the Ukrainian capital, Kiev, on
Wednesday was speaking after talks with Ukrainian President Leonid
Kuchma on the Russian economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time a French president has visited Ukraine
since it became independent seven years ago and was greeted in the
Ukrainian media as a display of "moral support".
</P>
<P>
On Thursday morning, the two presidents held talks and
signed four agreements on cooperation in the utilization of
nuclear energy, the power industry, nuclear safety, and the
administration of justice.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said France fully supported the 2.2 billion U.S. dollar,
three-year fund facility which the International Monetary Fund
(IMF) intended to provide Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The Ukraine government and the IMF reached a rough agreement in
July despite the IMF's caution amid the growing economic turmoil
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said the French President expressed an understanding of
Ukraine's desire to join the European Union. The two presidents
pledged to break down any artificial demarcation lines in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said the international community should help Russia
overcome the crisis and prevent it spreading to neighboring
states. He also pointed out that Russia should realize the
necessity for reform.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will hold further discussions with Kuchma before leaving
on Friday, for Kishinev, the capital of Moldova. 
</P>
