<HEADLINE> Over 300 Fires in Sri Lanka's Capital Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's capital Colombo
had over 300 fires during the first eight months of his year,
according to local fire department Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Colombo Fire Brigade sources said that they were called in
to snuff out 325 fires during this period. Most of the fires had
resulted from gas leaks and electrical short circuits.
</P>
<P>
There is an upward trend in the incidents in comparison to the
previous years.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 there were 426 fires and in 1997 there were 446. The
325 fire during the first eight months of this years is relatively
high compared with the two previous years, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The department receives at least two fire emergency calls each
day. The incidents varied from major fires to small fires which
nevertheless pose a threat to the public.
</P>
<P>
The Colombo fire Brigade has purchased three new fire engines
from Indonesia last month to strengthen the brigade. 
