<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Billions of Yuan Saved by Avoiding Flood Diversion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The reversal of a major flood
diversion decision last month helped save tens of billions of yuan
in economic losses, according to Chinese water conservation
experts.
</P>
<P>
The diversion was planned for August 16 when the Yangtze River
water level at Shashi in Hubei Province surpassed the danger level
of 45 meters.
</P>
<P>
A diversion would have resulted in the inundation of vast areas
of the Jinjiang River Flood Diversion Area, a developed area
covering 921 square kilometers with a population of
510,000. Because of the possible diversion, 350,000 people had
been evacuated.
</P>
<P>
According experts, the State Council made the final decision
against diverting floodwaters after taking into full consideration
the opinions of water conservation experts.
</P>
<P>
Based on scientific analysises, the experts concluded that the
flood crest would not last long enough to require a diversion.
</P>
<P>
"This indicates the central government leaders attach great
importance to scientific ideas," one expert said.
</P>
<P>
The experts also attributed the avoidance of the flood
diversion to the tenacious efforts of millions of flood-fighters
defending the Yangtze embankments and to sound flood-control
facilities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980904.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaria Ravages Ecuadorian Littoral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's health authorities
will implement an emergency plan of spraying its malaria-affected
areas, especially the coastal areas, health authorities said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Malaria cases have increased in Ecuador during recent
weeks. So far there have been 19,427 laboratory confirmed cases,
of which about 15,000 happened in littoral provinces, such as
Esmeraldas, Manabi, Guaya, and El Oro, Malaria Eradication Service
(SNEM) medics said.
</P>
<P>
Esmeraldas has had 2,942 cases of falsiparum malaria and 2,036
cases of vivax; Manabi, 2,296 cases of falsiparum and 995 cases of
vivax; Guayas, 308 and 681 cases respectively, and in El Oro,
1,078 cases of malignant malaria among its 5,221 malaria cases.
</P>
<P>
The Public Health Ministry announced the import of medicine and
chemical supplements to cope with the malaria-epidemic in coastal
areas.
</P>
<P>
SNEN medics said that so far, imported medicines, worth one
million U.S.dollars, had not arrived, and the situation could
worsen and even get out of control if they failed to arrive.
</P>
</TEXT>
