<HEADLINE> Rio Summit Aims for Region's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The 12th Summit of the
Group of Rio will give preference in its working agenda to the
sustained development of Latin America, Adan Castillo Galastica,
Panama's Livestock Development Ministry spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Castillo, who is attending this international event as an
observer, highlighted the need for promoting the socio-economic
development of Latin America, which is being hit by a serious
financial crisis because of the situations in Asia and Russia.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting of the Latin American presidents, members of the
Group of Rio, will have a positive effect on the regional
economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the Community of Andean Nations (CNA) and
members of the regional consultation organization, will also
discuss the theme of tariff elimination in exports of soy beans,
during the meeting of heads of state.
</P>
<P>
The CNA ministers of commerce will hold a parallel meeting to
analyze the development of liberalization of their markets, and
increased commercial integration among its members.
</P>
<P>
The Group of Rio presidents will establish new security
mechanisms and will seek ways to make the region a zone of peace,
free from mass destruction weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
