<HEADLINE> China Seeks Dominance at Military Pentathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China is seeking to continue
its domination in the World Military Pentathlon Championship
slated from September 10-16 here.
</P>
<P>
A ten-member team has been formed and it is favored to sweep
the team and individual titles in the annual military event.
</P>
<P>
China's men team, which was set up in 1980, has pocketed ten
group titles and five silver medals, as well as six individual
trophies, while their women's counterparts has brought home four
team gold, two silver and five individual gold medals since 1991.
</P>
<P>
China dominated last edition of the event by taking the both
the men's and women's team title in Sweden, while Wang Lianying
won her fourth straight women's individual title.
</P>
<P>
A total of 187 athletes from 25 countries and regions will
compete in the last major military sport gala this century, with
South Africa and the United Arab Emirates as inspectors.
</P>
<P>
The championship features six events for team and individual
competitions, including the 500-meter obstacle rallies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
