<HEADLINE> Chile's Exports Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chile's exports amounted to
8.909 billion U.S. dollars during the first seven months of 1998,
a 12.7 percent drop compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Affairs Ministry's Exports Promotion Direction said
that the biggest drop was registered in the sales to Asia, with a
reduction of 36.1 percent, totaling 2.315 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Japan and South Korea were 1.197 billion dollars and
216 million dollars, reductions of 27.1 percent and 59 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The only Asian nation where Chilean exports continued growing
was China which had imports valued at 241 million dollars, a 42.1
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Mercosur dropped by 9.8 percent to a total of 959
million dollars, while those to the North America Free Trade
Agreement area dropped 1.3 percent to 1.916 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The only zone where Chilean exports increased in the period of
January-July of 1998 was the European Union, where imports
increased by 1.9 percent to 2.441 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
