<HEADLINE> Ma's Family Army to Miss Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Controversial Chinese
athletics coach Ma Junren will not lead his renowned family army
to this year's Asian Games in Thailand, the country's athletics
authorities confirmed here today.
</P>
<P>
Ma and his women middle and long distance runners have been
automatically disqualified from competing at the Bangkok Asian
Games in December after they skipped the national athletics
championships, which is ongoing here to serve as the
qualification event for the Games, vice-manager of the national
athletics administration center Shang Xiutang said.
</P>
<P>
"We will not change the rules to let Ma's team to go," Shang
insisted.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also accused Ma, who failed to bring his world
record-beating team to any of this season's national Grand Prix
event, of ignoring the sports rules and said he missed the
continental sports gala only with himself to blame.
</P>
<P>
An athlete must attend at least two out of six nationl Grand
Prix events and finish in the top eight in the overall standings
to qualify for the Grand Prix finals, which send its top athletes
to the national championships.
</P>
<P>
It has been reported in some media that Ma has lost interest
in competing at the continental events and now has only the 2000
Olympics on his agenda.
</P>
<P>
Last October, Ma guided his team to shatter 5000m race world
record twice in the National Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
