<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fairly Strong Quake Hits Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake
measuring 4.6 on the open-ended Richter scale jolted Miyazaki
Prefecture in southwestern Japan Friday morning, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties. No
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 8:02 a.m. (local time), was
centered about 40 kilometers under the seabed in Hyuga, the agency
said. 
</P>
