<HEADLINE> U.S. Closes More Overseas Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Defense Department
announced on Thursday that it is returning three military
installations in Germany and a hospital in Israel to those nations.
</P>
<P>
The moves will affect 92 Defense Department employees and 150
local nationals, the Pentagon said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the sites will be vacated by U.S. forces and
returned to the control of the host nations as part of the
Pentagon's 23rd round of closures of overseas facilities.
</P>
<P>
In Germany, they are Eselfuerth Quartermaster Facility in
Kaiserslautern, Lohnsfeld Communication Station in Mannheim and
Kreuzberg Maintenance Facility in Ramstein, all managed by the
U.S. Army Europe.
</P>
<P>
