<HEADLINE> Stone Forest to Have New Look with Imported Laser Devices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province will highlight the night scene of its unique
"Stone Forest" with advanced computerized laser devices
imported from Britain.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Yunnan provincial government said the
colorful night scenes are specially designed for the International
Gardening Fair that will be held here from next May to October.
</P>
<P>
He said the 8-million-U.S.-dollar devices will create scenes
such as "the birth of the stone forest," "volcanic eruption,"
"glittering diamonds," water curtains and music fountains.
</P>
<P>
The Stone Forest is 120 kilometers southeast of Kunming,
capital of Yunnan Province, and one of the world's wonders with
its karst topography, ethnic customs and traditions. Tens of
millions of tourists visit the Stone Forest each year.
</P>
<P>
However, the picturesque area is pitch-dark at night.
</P>
<P>
This light at night project is expected to be completed before
the opening of next year's gardening fair.  
</P>
