<HEADLINE> US Reports Rapid Reduction of Land Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of land mines
worldwide has declined rapidly thanks to international efforts,
leading to an expectation that the world could get rid of it in
years rather than decades, the United States State Department said
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a report entitled "Hidden Killers 1998: The Global Landmine
Crisis," the State Department said more accurate information shows
that the number of land mines is 30 to 50 percent fewer than
originally projected. Initial estimates put the number at 100
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
